definition.value: An amino acid zwitterion resulting from a transfer of a proton from the carboxy group to the amino group of N(5)-phenyl-L-glutamine; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 2-hydroxy-7-methoxy-5-methyl-1-naphthoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
An EC 1.3.1.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor CH-CH group, NAD(+) or NADP(+) as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of acyl-CoA dehydrogenase (NADP(+)), EC 1.3.1.8.

A zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the 5-hydroxy to the tertiary amino group of 2-deoxy-alpha-L-fucosylaclacinomycin S. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
An EC 2.5.1.* (non-methyl-alkyl or aryl transferase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of UDP-N-acetylglucosamine 1-carboxyvinyltransferase (EC 2.5.1.7).
An EC 3.5.4.* (non-peptide cyclic amidine C-N hydrolase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of cytosine deaminase (EC 3.5.4.1).

label.value: EC 5.1.2.* (racemases acting on hydroxy acids and derivatives) inhibitor

definition.value: An EC 5.1.* (racemase/epimerase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any such enzyme acting on hydroxy acids and their derivatives (EC 5.1.2.*).

label.value: EC 5.1.3.* (racemases acting on carbohydrates and derivatives) inhibitor

definition.value: An EC 5.1.* (racemase/epimerase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any such enzyme acting on carbohydrates and their derivatives (EC 5.1.3.*).

label.value: EC 5.1.99.* (racemases acting on other compounds) inhibitor

definition.value: An EC 5.1.* (racemase/epimerase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any such enzyme acting compounds other than amino acids and their derivatives, hydroxy acids and their derivatives, or carbohydrates and their derivatives (EC 5.1.99.*).
An EC 5.1.3.* (racemases acting on carbohydrates and derivatives) inhibitor that interferes with the action of UDP-glucose 4-epimerase (EC 5.1.3.2).
A 1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-palmityl-2-acetyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
An aromatic ether that is the 2-benzylphenyl ether of 2-(piperidin-1-yl)propanol.
A 2-acyl-1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are hexadecyl and acetyl respectively; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-[1-(2-benzylphenoxy)propan-2-yl]piperidine that has R configuration. The racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-benproperine is used as a cough suppressant.
A 1-[1-(2-benzylphenoxy)propan-2-yl]piperidine that has S configuration. The racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-benproperine is used as a cough suppressant.
A 1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the alkyl group at C-1 is specified as hexadecyl.
An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the nitrogen of (R)-benproperine.
An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the nitrogen of (S)-benproperine.
An organoammonium phosphate resulting from the formal reaction of equimolar amounts of (R)-benproperine and phosphoric acid.
An organoammonium phosphate resulting from the formal reaction of equimolar amounts of (S)-benproperine and phosphoric acid.
An ionic macromolecule obtained by deprotonation of the terminal carboxy group of poly(6-aminohexanoic acid).
A member of the class of benzoates obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any 4-hydroxy-3-polyprenylbenzoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

An aminouracil that is D-ribitol in which the hydroxy group at position 1 is substituted by the 6-amino group of 6-amino-5-(2-oxoethylideneamino)uracil. Unstable mucosal-associated invariant T (MAIT)-activating antigen, formed by non-enzymatic reaction between 5-amino-6-D-ribitylaminouracil and glyoxal.

An aminouracil that is D-ribitol in which the hydroxy group at position 1 is substituted by the 6-amino group of 6-amino-5-(2-oxopropylideneamino)uracil. Unstable mucosal-associated invariant T (MAIT)-activating antigen, formed by non-enzymatic reaction between 5-amino-6-D-ribitylaminouracil and methylglyoxal.
The trans-isomer of  benzylideneacetone. It acts as an inhibitor of the enzyme phospholipase A2 (EC 3.1.1.4) of insects like diamond back moth.
The cis-isomer of benzylideneacetone.
A 1-alkyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-oleyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
The  (2S)-enantiomer of ethyl hydroxy(phenyl)acetate.
The (2R)-enantiomer of ethyl hydroxy(phenyl)acetate.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-ethyl mandelate.

A nucleoside triphosphate analogue that is GTP in which the oxygen atom bridging the beta- to the gamma- phosphate is replaced by a nitrogen atom A non-hydrolyzable analog of GTP, it binds tightly to G-protein in the presence of Mg(2+).
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and phosphonate OH groups of guanosine 5'-[beta,gamma-imido]triphosphate.

A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is henicosane in which a hydrogen attached to one of the terminal carbons is replaced by a hydroxy group. It has been isolated from the aerial parts of Siegesbeckia orientalis and from an Italian bread wheat variety, Pegaso, and its 11 near-isogenic lines.

A very long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is tricosane in which a hydrogen attached to one of the terminal carbons is replaced by a hydroxy group. It has been isolated from bulbs of Polianthes tuberosa, bran from the Italian bread wheat variety Pegaso and its 11 near-isogenic lines, and from the aerial parts of Centaurea austro-anatolica.
The cis-stereoisomer of anethole.

A member of the class of pyrimidobenzodiazepines that is 5,11-dimethylpyrimido[4,5-b][1,4]benzodiazepin-6-one carrying at C-2 on the pyrimidine ring a 4-[(4-methylpiperazin-1-yl)piperidine-1-carbonyl]-2-methoxyanilino substituent. It is an inhibitor of the Parkinson's disease kinase LRRK2.

A member of the class of aminopyrimidines that is 2,6-diamino-5-chloropyrimidine in which the amino groups at positions 2 and 6 are respectively carrying 2-methoxy-4-(morpholin-4-yl)phenyl and 2-(methanesulfonylamino)phenyl substituents. It is an inhibitor of the Parkinson's disease kinase LRRK2.
An anion of a trioxilin formed by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid moiety.
A member of the class of quinolines that is 1,2,3,4-tetrahydroquinoline which is substituted at positions 2, 6, and 7 by (isopropylamino)methyl, hydroxymethyl, and nitro groups, respectively.
A {2-[(isopropylamino)methyl]-7-nitro-1,2,3,4-tetrahydroquinolin-6-yl}methanol that has R configuration.
A {2-[(isopropylamino)methyl]-7-nitro-1,2,3,4-tetrahydroquinolin-6-yl}methanol that has S configuration.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acetyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the alk-1-enyl group has Z geochemistry.

A member of the class of flavonols that is kaempferol which is substituted at position 8 by a 3-methylbut-2-en-1-yl group and in which the hydroxy groups at positions 3, 4', and 7 have been converted to the corresponding 6-deoxy-alpha-L-mannopyranoside, methyl ether, and beta-D-glucopyranoside, respectively. A phoshphodiesterase-5 inhibitor, it is obtained from several species of plants in the genus Epimedium and is thought to be the main active ingredient of the Chinese herbal medicine Herba Epimedii (yinyanghuo).
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 1-acyl group is specified as oleoyl.
A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine(1-) in which the 1-acyl group is specified as oleoyl.
An 11-hydroxylaurate obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of (11R)-hydroxylauric acid; major species at pH 7.3.
An omega-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 18-hydroxyoleic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An organosulfate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the sulfate group of 1-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl)-N-acylsphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.

A very long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is pentacosane in which a hydrogen attached to one of the terminal carbons is replaced by a hydroxy group. It has been identified in the roots of Rhodiola imbricata.
